text: Wiebke Silge (born 16 July 1996 in Münster) is a German volleyball player. She played for the German national volleyball team. She played at the 2014 Montreux Volley Masters, 2014 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2014 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2015 Montreux Volley Masters, 2015 FIVB World Grand Prix, and 2016 European Olympic Qualification Tournament. She played for USC Münster, SC Potsdam, and VC Kanti Schaffhausen. == References == Category:1996 births Category:German volleyball players Category:Sportspeople from North Rhine-Westphalia Category:People from Münster Category:Living people
